# OenoBoost — Project Rules

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router only — never use Pages Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript strict (`strict: true` in tsconfig)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v3 + Shadcn/ui (components in `components/ui/`)
- **Backend**: Supabase (PostgreSQL) — no ORM, raw SQL queries via Supabase client
- **Auth**: Supabase Auth
- **Map**: Mapbox GL JS
- **Deployment**: Vercel

## Folder Structure

```
app/                        # Next.js routing ONLY — zero business logic here
  (auth)/                   # Auth route group (login, register, reset-password)
  (app)/                    # Protected route group (main app)
    vignoble/
    cepages/
    sols/
    vinification/
    degustation/
    dictionnaire/
    quiz/
    profil/
  layout.tsx
  globals.css

features/                   # Business logic by module — the core of the app
  vignoble/
    components/             # Module-specific components
    hooks/                  # Module-specific React hooks
    queries/                # All Supabase query functions for this module
    types.ts                # Module TypeScript types
  cepages/
  sols/
  vinification/
  degustation/
  dictionnaire/
  quiz/
  auth/

components/                 # Global reusable UI components
  ui/                       # Shadcn/ui (auto-generated — never edit manually)
  shared/                   # Custom global components (Navbar, Footer, PremiumGate, etc.)

lib/                        # Pure utilities, no state
  supabase/
    client.ts               # Supabase browser client
    server.ts               # Supabase server client (for Server Components)
  utils/
    i18n.ts                 # Translation helper (see rule 03-i18n)
    cn.ts                   # clsx + tailwind-merge wrapper

types/                      # Global shared TypeScript types
  database.ts               # Types generated from Supabase schema
  globals.ts                # Global types (Locale, UserPlan, UserRole, etc.)
```

## Naming Conventions

- **Component files**: `kebab-case.tsx` — e.g. `wine-card.tsx`, `premium-gate.tsx`
- **Hook files**: `use-kebab-case.ts` — e.g. `use-locale.ts`
- **Query files**: `kebab-case.queries.ts` — e.g. `vignoble.queries.ts`
- **React components**: `PascalCase` for the function name — e.g. `export default function WineCard()`
- **Types & interfaces**: `PascalCase` — e.g. `WineRegion`, `UserProfile`
- **Constants**: `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` — e.g. `MAX_FREE_FAVORITES`

## Component Rules

- **Server Components by default** — only add `"use client"` when strictly necessary (interactivity, browser APIs, hooks)
- **No business logic in `app/` pages** — pages only import and compose feature components
- **No direct Supabase calls in components** — always go through `features/[module]/queries/`
- **No hardcoded colors or spacing** — always use Tailwind tokens or CSS variables defined in the design system

## Key Application Concepts

### Freemium
- Users have a `plan` field: `'free'` or `'premium'`
- Free users: access to 20% of content, max 5 favorites, no advanced quiz, no tasting sheet
- Always wrap premium content with the `<PremiumGate>` component
- Never enforce freemium limits in the database — enforce in the application layer

### Bilingual Content
- All editorial content has `_fr` and `_en` column variants in the database
- User locale is stored in `users.locale` (`'fr'` or `'en'`)
- Always use the `getContent(obj, field, locale)` helper — never access `_fr`/`_en` directly in components

### Content Status
- All content tables have a `status` field: `'draft'` | `'published'` | `'archived'`
- Only query `status = 'published'` content on the public-facing platform
- The CMS (separate repo at `cms.oenoboost.com`) handles draft/archived content

### Soft Delete
- Content tables have a `deleted_at` timestamp column
- Always filter `deleted_at IS NULL` in queries — never show soft-deleted content

## Database

- **Primary keys**: UUID v4 (`id`)
- **Foreign keys**: `{singular_table}_id` — e.g. `region_id`, `user_id`
- **Booleans**: prefixed with `is_` — e.g. `is_premium`, `is_verified`
- **Emails**: always normalized with `LOWER()` on insert and query
- **Geographic data**: `geojson JSONB` + `centroid_lat` / `centroid_lng DOUBLE PRECISION` for Mapbox
